resources.string: CONTENT : Tirumala is a census town in Chittoor district of the Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. The town is a part of Tirupati Urban Development Authority and located in Tirupati (rural) mandal of Tirupati revenue division.[5] It is a hill town where Tirumala Venkateswara Temple is located, which is the abode of Lord Venkateswara.

Kapila Theertham temple is the only Shiva temple in the vicinity of Tirupati. It is also said to be one of the 108 sacred teerthas (springs) on Tirumala hills. The Siva lingam here is made of brass. A huge stone statue of a seated bull Nandhi, greets devotees at the entrance to the temple.

CONTENT : Kapila Theertham is a famous Saivite Temple and Theertham, located at Tirupati in the Chittoor District of Andhra Pradesh, India. The idol is believed to be installed by Kapila Muni and hence Lord Siva here is referred to as Kapileswara.

CONTENT : Sri Venkateswara Zoological Park has been established on modern concepts of Zoo ... The Park is named after the Lord Venkateswara of Seven Hills in Tirupati and the Zoo contains so many animals and saperately it contain Lion Safari.

CONTENT : Padmavathi Temple[1] is the temple dedicated to Goddess Padmavathi or Alamelumanga, the consort of Lord Venkateswara. The Temple is situated in Tiruchanur, at a distance of 5 km from Tirupati in Chittoor district of Andhra Pradesh, India. The Temple is being administered by Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams.

CONTENT : Sri Govindarajaswamy Temple is an ancient Hindhu-vaishnavite temple situated at the heart of the Tirupati city in Chittoor District of Andhra Pradesh state in India. The temple was built during 12 century and was consecrated in the year 1130 AD by Saint Ramanujacharya.[1] The temple is one of the earliest structures in Tirupati and also one of the biggest temple complex in Chittoor district. The Tirupati(down hill) city is built around this temple. The temple at current is being administered by Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams.

CONTENT : Tirupati Iskon Temple is a beautiful temple of Lord Krishna . The architecture of the temple is very beautiful . We can spend hours in the temple seeing the Deities , Architecture and the paintings. It is good to visit the temple in the evening hours to experience the beauty of the temple.

CONTENT : Srikalahasti is a holy town in Chittoor district of the Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. ... The town is a part of Tirupati Urban Development Authority, which is located on the banks of the River Swarnamukhi. The town is known for Srikalahasteeswara Temple dedicated to Shiva representing one of the Pancha Bhoota Sthalams.

CONTENT : Sri Venkateswara University College of Engineering was established as a constituent college of the Sri Venkateswara University, Tirupati, in the year 1959. Tirupati, the temple town lies at foot-hills of Tirumala, the abode of Sri Venkateswara, the Lord of Seven-hills.
